  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large clay pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and saut\u00118e until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute.",
    "Add the chicken breast and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes.",
    "Add the chilli powder, cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the sliced red bell pepper and cook for an additional 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the chickpeas, preserved lemon, and 2 cups of water. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20-25 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Stir in some chopped fresh parsley before serving.",
    "Serve hot over couscous or rice."
